<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 8:10PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Bedford and Amherst counties and the city of Lynchburg through 845
PM EDT...
At 809 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boonsboro, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Amherst...
Forks Of Buffalo...
Clifford...
Forest...
Madison Heights...
and Boonsboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
